            . I am the <rs id="t18290409-311-viclabel1758" type="occupation">wife</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-311-victim2837 t18290409-311-viclabel1758"></join> of 
               <persName id="t18290409-311-person2838">
                  James 
                  Hazel
               <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2838" type="surname" value="Hazel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2838" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2838" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             - we live in <placeName id="t18290409-311-crimeloc1759">Jewin-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-311-crimeloc1759" type="placeName" value="Jewin-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-311-crimeloc1759" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-311-off1757 t18290409-311-crimeloc1759"></join>. On the 24th of February the prisoner came to our shop, and offered what appeared to be a half-sovereign, in payment for a milliner's doll, which came to 2s. 6d; I gave him 7s. 6d. change - I put the half-sovereign into my till; there was no other money there - I afterwards gave it to Mr. Harris.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Are you sure there was no other money in the till? A. Yes - I gave the change from my pocket: I did not know him before- I am not mistaken in his person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-311-person2839">
                  JAMES 
                  HARRIS
               <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2839" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2839" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2839" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the room adjoining the shop - Hazell showed me this coin; I pursued, and took the prisoner, who had gone through some courts leading to Whitecross-street - he was walking; I said we wanted him, he had been passing a bad half-sovereign - he said,"If it is a had one, I took it, and don't want any brother about it, I will give you another;" I said, "We think you knew it was a bad one" - we took him into a public-house, where the officer took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-311-person2840">
                  DANIEL 
                  USALL
               <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2840" type="surname" value="USALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2840" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2840" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a haberdasher, and live in Aldersgate-street. On the 24th of February, between twelve and one o'clock, the prisoner came to look at a pair of gloves; he selected a pair, and threw down what appeared to be a half-sovereign - I said we had not change; he said, "I will call again in a few minutes, if you will wrap them up, and get me a riding-belt in the mean time" - I followed him, and watched him into Hazel's shop; there was another person with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-311-person2841">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BETTERTON
               <interp inst="t18290409-311-person2841" type="surname" value="BETTERTON"></interp>
